sections.title: Indication
sections.value:
Asymptomatic screening.  No known clinical problems.  Bilateral breast implants.

Last known clinical exam: Unknown.

sections.title: Technique
sections.value: CC and MLO and implant displaced images obtained by full-field digital technique with tomosynthesis and analyzed with Computer-Aided Detection (CAD). 3D mammographic/tomosynthesis and C-View images were obtained. 3D post-processed and C-View images were reviewed on an independent workstation.

sections.title: Findings
sections.value:
Bilateral breast implants intact without contour deformity.

No suspicious masses, calcifications, architectural distortion or other findings.  No suspicious skin or nipple changes.  No suspicious axillary lymph nodes.

sections.title: Impression
sections.value:
No mammographic evidence of malignancy.  If there are no clinical concerns, routine annual screening mammography is advised.

The patient and physician will receive the results by fax and/or mail.

ACR CATEGORY: BI-RADS 2: Benign.

TISSUE DENSITY:   

RECOMMENDED FOLLOW UP:  Routine annual screening mammography is advised.

RECALL INTERVAL:  1 YR SCREENING     

RECALL TYPE:  MAMMO
